-- Indian shares ends lower; banks fall
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 06:09AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell nearly 1 percent on Wednesday, snapping two days of gains, as lenders such as State Bank of India and ICICI Bank slumped on worries that a sell-off in government bonds would hit the value of their debt holdings.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 0.95  percent lower at 25,660.84, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> fell 0.96 percent to 7,672.05.